    "When β → 0, all the probability mass will focus on the response with the highest reward.",
    "On the other extreme, when β → ∞, the optimal policy will be the same as the reference policy π ref (y|x).",
    "Due to the discrete nature of language generation, we typically optimize RLHF objective in Equation (2) using RL algorithms, such as PPO (Ouyang et al., 2022; Schulman et al., 2017).",
    "Although RLHF with PPO has achieved remarkable success, the training process of PPO is unstable because of the high variance of the optimization (Engstrom et al., 2020; Xiao and Wang, 2021).",
